===Etymology===
First attested in the late 14th century. From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|acusacion|lang=fro}} (French {{term|accusation|lang=fr}}), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|accūsātiō||accusation, indictment}}, from {{m|la|accūsō||blame, accuse}}. More at {{term|accuse|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˌæk.jʊ.ˈzeɪ.ʃən/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-accusation.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʃən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of [[accusing]].
#* {{quote-book|author=Shakespeare|title=Henry VIII, III-i|passage=We come not by the way of '''accusation''' / To taint that honor every good tongue blesses.}}
# {{context|legal|lang=en}} A [[formal]] [[charge]] brought against a person in a [[court of law]].
#: [They] set up over his head his '''accusation''' - ''Matthew 27:37''
# An [[allegation]].

